!!! Entropy

Entropy is the lab server.  The machine is a Linux box and sits down in the machine room in the CSCF area of the building.

There are 3 types of partitions on entropy.
* *User Partitions* - each student has a home directory on a user partition.  These partitions are backed up frequently.  Typically there is not a lot of space on the user partitions so people should consider what they keep around in their home directory.  The best use for this directory is programs and projcts that you are currently working on.  Things like Mp3s should not be stored in this directory for any reason.
* *Project/Data Partitions* - these partitions are backed up once a week.  Typically data for large experiments should be saved here.  Note p4 is offlimits for people to use as their data directory.  It has been reserved for group software and data that will be shared by students working on joint projects.
* *Scratch Partitions* - these partitions are never backed up.  Typically old projects and old class data can go on these partitions.

Note each desk computer also typically has large scratch partitions that may also be used.  This is where people typically store the MP3s they listen to at work.

